{"ts": "2026-07-13T21:04:51.041+00:00", "event": "request", "attempt": 1, "n_messages": 1, "roles": ["user"], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Build a mini spreadsheet as a single self-contained web app.\n\nGrid: 10 columns (A–J) × 10 rows (1–10). Every cell is an `<input>` element\nwith id `cell-A1` … `cell-J10`, laid out as a proper grid with row/column\nheaders. The visible app must be at least 600×400 px.\n\nBehavior:\n- A cell holds either a plain value or a formula starting with `=`.\n- Formulas support numbers, cell references (`A1`), `+ - * /`, and\n  parentheses, with normal operator precedence: `=2+3*4` is 14,\n  `=(2+3)*4` is 20, `=A1*2+B2` works.\n- When a cell is not being edited it displays its COMPUTED value; clicking\n  into it shows the raw text for editing; Enter or clicking away commits.\n- Recalculation is automatic and transitive: changing `A1` immediately\n  updates every cell whose formula depends on it, directly or through other\n  cells.\n- Circular references display exactly `#CYCLE` in every cell of the cycle.\n- Invalid formulas (bad syntax, reference to a non-cell) display `#ERR`.\n- Non-numeric plain text displays as itself; empty cells count as 0 inside\n  formulas.\n- An **Export CSV** button with id `export` writes the current 10×10 grid of\n  COMPUTED values into a `<textarea id=\"csv\">` (comma-separated, one line\n  per row).\n\nScripting API (for automated grading — must work exactly as specified):\n\n    window.sheet.set(\"B2\", \"=A1*2\")   // enter text into a cell, as if typed\n    window.sheet.get(\"B2\")            // -> the DISPLAYED string, e.g. \"10\"\n    window.sheet.raw(\"B2\")            // -> the raw text, e.g. \"=A1*2\"\n\nNo dead UI: every visible control must actually work. No external resources.\n\n\nRespond with a single fenced ```html code block containing the complete contents of app.html — one fully self-contained file with all CSS and JavaScript inline. No external resources (no CDNs, fonts, or images). Do not include anything outside the code block."}]}
{"ts": "2026-07-13T21:07:43.435+00:00", "event": "response", "attempt": 1, "text": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Mini Spreadsheet</title>\n<style>\n  #app { width: 600px; height: 400px; overflow: auto; font-family: sans-serif; }\n  table { border-collapse: collapse; }\n  th, td { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 2px; text-align: center; }\n  th { background: #f0f0f0; }\n  .cell-input { width: 50px; height: 24px; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: right; border: none; outline: none; background: transparent; }\n  .cell-input:focus { background: #fff; }\n  #export { margin-top: 10px; padding: 4px 8px; }\n  #csv { width: 100%; height: 100px; margin-top: 10px; font-family: monospace; box-sizing: border-box; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div id=\"app\"></div>\n<script>\nconst COLS = 10, ROWS = 10;\nlet rawValues = [];\nlet inputs = [];\nlet currentComputedCache = new Map();\n\nfunction colToLetter(c) { return String.fromCharCode(65 + c); }\nfunction letterToCol(l) { return l.toUpperCase().charCodeAt(0) - 65; }\nfunction cellKey(col, row) { return colToLetter(col) + (row + 1); }\n\n// ---------- Tokenizer ----------\nfunction tokenize(str) {\n  const tokens = [];\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < str.length) {\n    const ch = str[i];\n    if (/\\s/.test(ch)) { i++; continue; }\n    if (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9' || ch === '.') {\n      let j = i, dot = false;\n      while (j < str.length) {\n        const c = str[j];\n        if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') j++;\n        else if (c === '.' && !dot) { dot = true; j++; }\n        else break;\n      }\n      tokens.push({ type: 'NUMBER', value: parseFloat(str.slice(i, j)) });\n      i = j;\n    } else if (/[A-Za-z]/.test(ch)) {\n      let j = i + 1;\n      while (j < str.length && /[0-9]/.test(str[j])) j++;\n      const ref = str.slice(i, j).toUpperCase();\n      const col = letterToCol(ref[0]);\n      const row = parseInt(ref.slice(1)) - 1;\n      if (col < 0 || col >= COLS || row < 0 || row >= ROWS) throw new Error('Invalid reference');\n      tokens.push({ type: 'CELL_REF', col, row });\n      i = j;\n    } else if (ch === '+') { tokens.push({ type: 'PLUS' }); i++; }\n    else if (ch === '-') { tokens.push({ type: 'MINUS' }); i++; }\n    else if (ch === '*') { tokens.push({ type: 'MUL' }); i++; }\n    else if (ch === '/') { tokens.push({ type: 'DIV' }); i++; }\n    else if (ch === '(') { tokens.push({ type: 'LPAREN' }); i++; }\n    else if (ch === ')') { tokens.push({ type: 'RPAREN' }); i++; }\n    else throw new Error('Invalid character');\n  }\n  tokens.push({ type: 'EOF' });\n  return tokens;\n}\n\n// ---------- Parser ----------\nclass Parser {\n  constructor(tokens) { this.tokens = tokens; this.pos = 0; }\n  peek() { return this.tokens[this.pos]; }\n  consume(type) {\n    const t = this.peek();\n    if (t.type !== type) throw new Error(`Expected ${type}`);\n    this.pos++;\n    return t;\n  }\n  parse() {\n    const node = this.expr();\n    this.consume('EOF');\n    return node;\n  }\n  expr() {\n    let node = this.term();\n    while (this.peek().type === 'PLUS' || this.peek().type === 'MINUS') {\n      const op = this.peek().type;\n      this.consume(op);\n      node = new BinaryOp(node, op, this.term());\n    }\n    return node;\n  }\n  term() {\n    let node = this.factor();\n    while (this.peek().type === 'MUL' || this.peek().type === 'DIV') {\n      const op = this.peek().type;\n      this.consume(op);\n      node = new BinaryOp(node, op, this.factor());\n    }\n    return node;\n  }\n  factor() {\n    const t = this.peek();\n    if (t.type === 'NUMBER') { this.consume('NUMBER'); return new NumNode(t.value); }\n    if (t.type === 'CELL_REF') { this.consume('CELL_REF'); return new RefNode(t.col, t.row); }\n    if (t.type === 'LPAREN') { this.consume('LPAREN'); const n = this.expr(); this.consume('RPAREN'); return n; }\n    if (t.type === 'MINUS') { this.consume('MINUS'); return new UnaryOp('-', this.factor()); }\n    if (t.type === 'PLUS') { this.consume('PLUS'); return this.factor(); }\n    throw new Error('Unexpected token');\n  }\n}\n\n// ---------- AST Nodes ----------\nclass NumNode {\n  constructor(v) { this.v = v; }\n  eval(ctx) { return { value: this.v, error: null }; }\n}\nclass RefNode {\n  constructor(c, r) { this.c = c; this.r = r; }\n  eval(ctx) { return ctx.computeCell(this.c, this.r); }\n}\nclass BinaryOp {\n  constructor(l, op, r) { this.l = l; this.op = op; this.r = r; }\n  eval(ctx) {\n    const L = this.l.eval(ctx); if (L.error) return L;\n    const R = this.r.eval(ctx); if (R.error) return R;\n    let v;\n    switch (this.op) {\n      case 'PLUS': v = L.value + R.value; break;\n      case 'MINUS': v = L.value - R.value; break;\n      case 'MUL': v = L.value * R.value; break;\n      case 'DIV': if (R.value === 0) return { value: 0, error: '#ERR' }; v = L.value / R.value; break;\n      default: return { value: 0, error: '#ERR' };\n    }\n    return { value: v, error: null };\n  }\n}\nclass UnaryOp {\n  constructor(op, n) { this.op = op; this.n = n; }\n  eval(ctx) {\n    const r = this.n.eval(ctx); if (r.error) return r;\n    return this.op === '-' ? { value: -r.value, error: null } : r;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction parseFormula(s) {\n  return new Parser(tokenize(s)).parse();\n}\n\n// ---------- Recalculation ----------\nfunction recalcAll() {\n  const cache = new Map();\n  const visiting = new Set();\n\n  function computeCell(col, row) {\n    const key = cellKey(col, row);\n    if (cache.has(key)) return cache.get(key);\n    if (visiting.has(key)) {\n      const res = { value: 0, error: '#CYCLE', display: '#CYCLE' };\n      cache.set(key, res);\n      return res;\n    }\n    visiting.add(key);\n    const raw = rawValues[row][col];\n    let result;\n    if (raw.startsWith('=')) {\n      try {\n        const ast = parseFormula(raw.slice(1).trim());\n        const ctx = { computeCell };\n        const ev = ast.eval(ctx);\n        if (ev.error) result = { value: 0, error: ev.error, display: ev.error };\n        else result = { value: ev.value, error: null, display: ev.value.toString() };\n      } catch (e) {\n        result = { value: 0, error: '#ERR', display: '#ERR' };\n      }\n    } else {\n      const disp = raw;\n      const num = parseFloat(raw);\n      result = { value: isNaN(num) ? 0 : num, error: null, display: disp };\n    }\n    visiting.delete(key);\n    cache.set(key, result);\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  for (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++)\n    for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++)\n      computeCell(c, r);\n\n  currentComputedCache = cache;\n\n  // Update DOM for non-focused cells\n  for (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++)\n    for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {\n      const inp = inputs[r][c];\n      if (inp !== document.activeElement) {\n        const comp = cache.get(cellKey(c, r));\n        if (comp) inp.value = comp.display;\n      }\n    }\n}\n\n// ---------- UI Setup ----------\nconst container = document.getElementById('app');\nconst table = document.createElement('table');\n\n// Header row\nconst thead = document.createElement('thead');\nconst hdr = document.createElement('tr');\nhdr.appendChild(document.createElement('th'));\nfor (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {\n  const th = document.createElement('th');\n  th.textContent = colToLetter(c);\n  hdr.appendChild(th);\n}\nthead.appendChild(hdr);\ntable.appendChild(thead);\n\n// Body rows\nconst tbody = document.createElement('tbody');\ninputs = Array.from({ length: ROWS }, () => Array(COLS));\nrawValues = Array.from({ length: ROWS }, () => Array(COLS).fill(''));\n\nfor (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++) {\n  const tr = document.createElement('tr');\n  const th = document.createElement('th');\n  th.textContent = r + 1;\n  tr.appendChild(th);\n  for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {\n    const td = document.createElement('td');\n    const inp = document.createElement('input');\n    inp.type = 'text';\n    inp.className = 'cell-input';\n    inp.id = `cell-${colToLetter(c)}${r+1}`;\n    inp.dataset.col = c;\n    inp.dataset.row = r;\n    td.appendChild(inp);\n    tr.appendChild(td);\n    inputs[r][c] = inp;\n  }\n  tbody.appendChild(tr);\n}\ntable.appendChild(tbody);\ncontainer.appendChild(table);\n\n// Export button & textarea\nconst btn = document.createElement('button');\nbtn.id = 'export';\nbtn.textContent = 'Export CSV';\ncontainer.appendChild(btn);\n\nconst ta = document.createElement('textarea');\nta.id = 'csv';\ncontainer.appendChild(ta);\n\n// ---------- Event Handlers ----------\nfunction commitCell(r, c) {\n  const inp = inputs[r][c];\n  const newRaw = inp.value.trim();\n  if (newRaw !== rawValues[r][c]) {\n    rawValues[r][c] = newRaw;\n    recalcAll();\n  } else {\n    // just refresh display from cache\n    const comp = currentComputedCache.get(cellKey(c, r));\n    if (comp) inp.value = comp.display;\n  }\n}\n\nfor (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++) {\n  for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {\n    const inp = inputs[r][c];\n    inp.addEventListener('focus', () => { inp.value = rawValues[r][c]; });\n    inp.addEventListener('blur', () => commitCell(r, c));\n    inp.addEventListener('keydown', e => {\n      if (e.key === 'Enter') {\n        e.preventDefault();\n        const newRaw = inp.value.trim();\n        if (newRaw !== rawValues[r][c]) rawValues[r][c] = newRaw;\n        recalcAll();\n        inp.blur();\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nbtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n  let csv = '';\n  for (let r = 0; r < ROWS; r++) {\n    const row = [];\n    for (let c = 0; c < COLS; c++) {\n      const comp = currentComputedCache.get(cellKey(c, r));\n      row.push(comp ? comp.display : '');\n    }\n    csv += row.join(',') + '\\n';\n  }\n  ta.value = csv.trim();\n});\n\n// ---------- Scripting API ----------\nwindow.sheet = {\n  set(id, raw) {\n    const col = letterToCol(id[0]);\n    const row = parseInt(id.slice(1)) - 1;\n    if (col < 0 || col >= COLS || row < 0 || row >= ROWS) return;\n    rawValues[row][col] = raw.trim();\n    recalcAll();\n  },\n  get(id) {\n    const col = letterToCol(id[0]);\n    const row = parseInt(id.slice(1)) - 1;\n    if (col < 0 || col >= COLS || row < 0 || row >= ROWS) return '';\n    const comp = currentComputedCache.get(cellKey(col, row));\n    return comp ? comp.display : '';\n  },\n  raw(id) {\n    const col = letterToCol(id[0]);\n    const row = parseInt(id.slice(1)) - 1;\n    if (col < 0 || col >= COLS || row < 0 || row >= ROWS) return '';\n    return rawValues[row][col];\n  }\n};\n\n// Initial calculation\nrecalcAll();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>", "stop_reason": "stop", "tokens_in": 548, "tokens_out": 13381, "total_ms": 172397.5, "ttft_ms": 2103.7, "cost_usd": 0, "served_by": "Nvidia", "tool_calls": []}
